contains(x, y) - Method in class ly.img.android.pesdk.backend.model.chunk.RelativeRectFast
Returns true if (x,y) is inside the rectangle. The left and top are considered to be inside, while the right and bottom are not. This means that for a x,y to be contained: left <= x < right and top <= y < bottom. An empty rectangle never contains any point.
contains(left, top, right, bottom) - Method in class ly.img.android.pesdk.backend.model.chunk.RelativeRectFast
Returns true iff the 4 specified sides of a rectangle are inside or equal to this rectangle. i.e. is this rectangle a superset of the specified rectangle. An empty rectangle never contains another rectangle.

This class stores information of an EXIF tag. For more information about defined EXIF tags, please read the Jeita EXIF 2.2 standard. Tags should be instantiated using ly.img.android.pesdk.backend.exif.Exify$buildTag(ly.img.android.pesdk.backend.exif.Exify.TAG,java.lang.Object).

Exify - Class in ly.img.android.pesdk.backend.exif
This class provides methods and constants for reading and writing jpeg file metadata. It contains a collection of ExifTags, and a collection of definitions for creating valid ExifTags. The collection of ExifTags can be updated by: reading new ones from a file, deleting or adding existing ones, or building new ExifTags from a tag definition. These ExifTags can be written to a valid jpeg image as exif metadata.

Exify.Orientation - Interface in ly.img.android.pesdk.backend.exif
Constants for {@see #ExifTagKey.ORIENTATION}. They can be interpreted as follows: TOP_LEFT is the normal orientation. TOP_RIGHT is a left-right mirror. BOTTOM_LEFT is a 180 degree rotation. BOTTOM_RIGHT is a top-bottom mirror. LEFT_TOP is mirrored about the top-left<->bottom-right axis. TOP_RIGHT is a 90 degree clockwise rotation. BOTTOM_LEFT is mirrored about the top-right<->bottom-left axis. BOTTOM_RIGHT is a 270 degree clockwise rotation.
